1
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:40,291
[NANA]
We've got a big day tomorrow.

2
00:00:40,375 --> 00:00:41,708
You ready to race Saisei?

3
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:42,750
[TAKERU]
Yeah.

4
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,833
We're going to win.

5
00:00:44,916 --> 00:00:46,875
It's what we've been
working toward.

6
00:00:48,166 --> 00:00:49,458
Takeru?

7
00:00:49,541 --> 00:00:51,000
[TAKERU]
Huh?

8
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:51,916
[RIKU gasps]

9
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:52,666
What's up?

10
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,833
Uh... I...

11
00:00:54,916 --> 00:00:58,666
Well, uh, I just
wanna say thanks.

12
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:00,041
For what?

13
00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:03,416
Y'know. I thought
Tomoe ruined Stride for me

14
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:07,500
'cause he made it a chore.
I hated it for a while.

15
00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:10,000
But now, running with you
and the rest of the team

16
00:01:10,083 --> 00:01:13,291
has made me realize
I love Stride.

17
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,875
In the beginning, I thought
you were hassling me

18
00:01:17,958 --> 00:01:20,625
but now I know you were helping
me get my act together.

19
00:01:20,708 --> 00:01:22,416
And I'm really glad you did.

20
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:26,208
I gotta say, I'm thankful you
guys forced me to join!

21
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,083
[TAKERU]
Not quite.

22
00:01:32,166 --> 00:01:33,166
[RIKU]
Uh...

23
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:35,000
[TAKERU]
Sure, Sakurai and I invited you.

24
00:01:35,083 --> 00:01:37,708
But the three of us were meant
to be in Stride together.

25
00:01:37,791 --> 00:01:39,000
I don't follow you.

26
00:01:39,083 --> 00:01:41,625
Uh. Hang on, are you
tryin' to say it's, like,

27
00:01:41,708 --> 00:01:44,125
our destiny or somethin'?

28
00:01:44,208 --> 00:01:46,083
No, I don't believe in destiny.

29
00:01:46,166 --> 00:01:47,625
[RIKU gasps]

30
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:51,583
I'm confident that we'll win
the End of Summer tournament.

31
00:01:51,666 --> 00:01:53,583
Because we made a--

32
00:01:59,083 --> 00:02:00,416
[TAKERU]
Tomorrow we face Saisei.

33
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:01,833
Let's win!

34
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:05,666
Ha!

35
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:06,708
[RIKU]
Uh.

36
00:02:08,875 --> 00:02:10,541
[NANA, RIKU]
Yeah!

37
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:50,708
[ANNOUNCER 11A]
The wait is over, folks!

38
00:03:50,791 --> 00:03:52,791
After a season of training
and preparation,

39
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:54,166
our teams are ready.

40
00:03:54,250 --> 00:03:58,208
The End of Summer semi-finals
are about to begin!

41
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:03,875
[CROWD cheers]

42
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:05,041
[ANNOUNCER 11A]
Smile Land is proud

43
00:04:05,125 --> 00:04:06,958
to be hosting this
year's competition!

44
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:09,583
Racing today we have
last year's semi-finalist,

45
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:13,125
also known as the popular
music group Galaxy Standard.

46
00:04:13,208 --> 00:04:15,916
It's Saisei Academy
High School of Kanagawa!

47
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,666
[CROWD cheering]

48
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:18,666
Y'hear that?!

49
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:20,083
The crowd's goin'
insane for 'em!

50
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:21,958
Almost feels like we're
the away team, you know?

51
00:04:22,041 --> 00:04:23,541
Yeah, those guys
have plenty of fans.

52
00:04:23,625 --> 00:04:24,791
[ANNOUNCER 11A]
And here's the one team

53
00:04:24,875 --> 00:04:26,916
everyone has an eye on.
A returning juggernaut

54
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,333
in the world of Stride, Honan
Academy High School of Tokyo!

55
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:32,041
Honan!

56
00:04:32,125 --> 00:04:33,791
[CROWD cheering]

57
00:04:33,875 --> 00:04:37,375
--This is great!
--Honan all the way!

58
00:04:37,458 --> 00:04:39,333
They're cheering for ya!

59
00:04:39,416 --> 00:04:41,500
It looks like we have fans, too!

60
00:04:41,583 --> 00:04:43,083
[HEATH]
Oh, man, this place is packed

61
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:45,500
and the energy from the crowd's
gettin' me hyped for the race!

62
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:46,875
Awesome!

63
00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:50,166
[HOZUMI] My heart's about
to jump out of my chest.

64
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:54,291
Hozumi. Enjoy the fresh air.

65
00:04:54,375 --> 00:04:57,291
The sun's shining
and the sky is clear.

66
00:04:57,375 --> 00:04:59,250
It's a perfect day for Stride.

67
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:01,625
[ANNOUNCER 11A] Ladies and
gentlemen, the time has come!

68
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:04,708
Which of our teams will move on
to the End of Summer finals?

69
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:05,916
No matter the result,

70
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,708
this will definitely be
a race to remember!

71
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:10,041
Yes!

72
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:12,333
Let's keep our heads up
and our eyes on the prize.

73
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:14,791
'Cause This is my last chance.

74
00:05:15,958 --> 00:05:18,833
[ANNOUNCER 11A] All right!
Let's get both teams onstage!

75
00:05:18,916 --> 00:05:20,625
You Ready to do this, Honan?

76
00:05:20,708 --> 00:05:22,208
[ALL]
Yeah!

77
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:29,541
All competitors,
bow to the opponent!

78
00:05:29,625 --> 00:05:31,833
[ALL] Let's all make
this a good match!

79
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:33,958
How ya doin' there, Hozumi?

80
00:05:34,041 --> 00:05:35,375
Since we're racin'
at Smile Land,

81
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:36,958
I say we run as
fast as we can

82
00:05:37,041 --> 00:05:39,375
but try to have fun
at the same time!

83
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:41,166
That's easy, you've got
such a great attitude

84
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,083
you make everything
fun, Banchan!

85
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:47,500
Yeah, guess I do!
Everything's ♪ fu-fu-fu-fun! ♪

86
00:05:47,583 --> 00:05:48,416
Now you!

87
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,375
♪ Fu-fu-fu-fun. ♪

88
00:05:50,458 --> 00:05:52,750
Why sing Beethoven's 5th?

89
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:55,458
Why not? May it inspire us
to follow our destinies

90
00:05:55,541 --> 00:05:58,291
and face our challenges
without fear!

91
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:01,125
[KAEDE]
Though I will always

92
00:06:01,208 --> 00:06:03,000
think of myself as
your biggest fan--

93
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:06,333
with utmost respect I'd like to
become a worthy competitor.

94
00:06:06,416 --> 00:06:08,416
I wanted to race but
only when I deserved

95
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,916
the privilege of facing you.

96
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,458
That's been my wish
for a long time now.

97
00:06:12,541 --> 00:06:15,833
Today I think I'm finally
prepared to make it happen.

98
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,666
I will not lose.

99
00:06:19,125 --> 00:06:20,916
How admirable.

100
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,791
That said, I have no
intention of losing, either.

101
00:06:24,875 --> 00:06:27,333
Please go easy on me,
Mr. Team Captain.

102
00:06:27,416 --> 00:06:31,458
Nice try but you're not gettin'
under my skin today, bro.

103
00:06:31,541 --> 00:06:33,916
Ever since we first met,
you've said you're determined

104
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,833
to help Reiji get to
the top, no matter what.

105
00:06:35,916 --> 00:06:37,250
Just wonderin' if
that's still true.

106
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:40,583
Absolutely. We're too
close to back down now.

107
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:45,041
Listen. Reiji and I have
somethin' in common.

108
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:47,000
If we lose this match,
it's over.

109
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:50,000
So I'm gonna run this race
like my life's on the line.

110
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:53,125
Heh. What, is that supposed
to intimidate me?

111
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:55,333
Enjoy running your last race.

112
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:59,000
[RIKU]
To throw salt on someone's game.

113
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:00,208
[ASUMA]
Huh?

114
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:01,750
[RIKU] It means to screw up
someone's plans.

115
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,875
In other words, by helping me
you could've messed up

116
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:07,125
your team's plans to win
the next match against us.

117
00:07:07,208 --> 00:07:09,541
[ASUMA] So you finally
looked it up, huh?

118
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:14,541
[ASUMA] Gotta say,
I'm glad you didn't quit, man.

119
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:17,416
Thanks for believin' in me and
remindin' me why I love Stride.

120
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,875
Sorry I have to
kick your butt today.

121
00:07:19,958 --> 00:07:21,208
Yeah, right!

122
00:07:21,291 --> 00:07:22,458
All joking aside,

123
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:25,208
I can't think of anyone
I'd rather run against.

124
00:07:27,208 --> 00:07:27,958
[REIJI]
Hey.

125
00:07:28,041 --> 00:07:29,916
This should be a good race.

126
00:07:31,416 --> 00:07:33,291
Yeah, I think so too.

127
00:07:33,375 --> 00:07:36,666
[REIJI laughs] I can sense
those hidden feelings again.

128
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:39,541
They're bubbling up
inside of you.

129
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,416
Remember what I said last time?

130
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,708
Make sure you set
them free today.

131
00:07:43,791 --> 00:07:45,083
[TAKERU]
I will.

132
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:48,833
You better not
chicken out on me.

133
00:07:48,916 --> 00:07:49,833
Never.

134
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:51,916
I'm ready to let them go.

135
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:56,000
[ANNOUNCER 11A]
All right, folks!

136
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:57,208
It won't be long now!

137
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:59,583
The moment of truth
is almost here!

138
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:01,708
In this round of the End
of Summer semi-finals

139
00:08:01,791 --> 00:08:05,041
it's Saisei versus Honan.
Who'll come out on top?

140
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:07,250
The runners have taken
their starting positions,

141
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:10,583
and in just a few seconds,
the battle will begin!

142
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,500
[ANNOUNCER 1B]
On your mark...

143
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:19,125
[ANNOUNCER 1B]
Get set...

144
00:08:22,583 --> 00:08:25,583
--[buzzing]
--[CROWD cheering]

145
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:27,166
[HOZUMI panting]

146
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:29,708
[BANTARO panting]

147
00:08:29,791 --> 00:08:31,791
[SHIZUMA] Well, here we go,
are you ready for this?

148
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:32,666
You bet!

149
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:33,916
I've been working really hard

150
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,833
to build trusting relationships
with the team.

151
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,750
Just like you suggested!

152
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:39,083
Nice.

153
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:41,250
You're much more confident
than you were before.

154
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,916
This should be an awesome race.
Good luck, Nana.

155
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
You, too!

156
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:46,208
Just know that we're
gonna hit you

157
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:47,916
with everything we
learned at camp!

158
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,625
We've come a long
way since then!

159
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:56,375
[BANTARO]
I'm closin' in, Hozumi!

160
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,458
[HOZUMI] I can't believe
we've made it all the way

161
00:08:58,541 --> 00:09:00,041
to the semi-finals.

162
00:09:00,125 --> 00:09:03,125
This is Heath and Kyosuke's last
chance to win End of Summer.

163
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:05,708
If I screw this up,
then it's all over!

164
00:09:05,791 --> 00:09:07,416
I've gotta do my best!

165
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,666
I've gotta get a lead for them!

166
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:10,708
[NANA]
Watch out, Hozumi!

167
00:09:10,791 --> 00:09:11,750
[HOZUMI gasps]

168
00:09:13,666 --> 00:09:15,750
[BANTARO]
Wee! Ha, ha, ha!

169
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:17,291
[HOZUMI]
No way!

170
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:19,041
[NANA] Don't worry about him!
Keep running straight ahead.

171
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:21,000
Take the high road!

172
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:22,791
It's close, Bantaro.
Stay sharp!

173
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:24,458
And I need you to--

174
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:27,250
Heh. Keep having fun!

175
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,250
[BANTARO] Aw yeah!
That's what I like to hear!

176
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,083
When you run with
a smile on your face

177
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:32,916
there's no
way you can lose!

178
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,458
[HOZUMI panting]

179
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:35,916
[NANA]
Okay, you're closing in!

180
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,208
Take it to full speed!
Trust Kyosuke!

181
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:43,958
[NANA]
Kyosuke. Get set!

182
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:45,166
He's coming in fast!

183
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:46,333
Ready.

184
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:47,166
[NANA]
Three!

185
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:48,125
Two!

186
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:49,208
One!

187
00:09:49,291 --> 00:09:50,333
Go!

188
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:58,041
[KYOSUKE]
Hozumi!

189
00:09:58,125 --> 00:09:58,958
Jump!

190
00:09:59,041 --> 00:10:00,083
[HOZUMI panting]

191
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,041
[KYOSUKE]
I'll catch you, I promise!

192
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:03,666
You have to trust me!

193
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:06,875
[HOZUMI]
I do, Kyosuke!

194
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:11,916
[ANNOUNCER 11A] Honan completes
a mid-air relation!

195
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,833
Kohinata was in a tight spot

196
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:16,250
but that miraculous
move just saved him!

197
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:17,083
The spirit of Stride...

198
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:18,541
That was awesome.

199
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:20,583
Way to go, guys.

200
00:10:20,666 --> 00:10:21,458
[BANTARO panting]

201
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:22,666
[HOZUMI sighs]

202
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,458
[BOTH laughing]

203
00:10:27,541 --> 00:10:29,416
[BOTH]
Nice one, bro!

204
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,250
[KAEDE panting]

205
00:10:36,916 --> 00:10:39,250
[KAEDE] I gotta run as fast
as I can to keep the lead!

206
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:42,375
If Kuga gets in front of me we
might never get ahead again!

207
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:43,666
[SHIZUMA]
He's coming up behind you!

208
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:45,125
[KAEDE gasping]

209
00:10:47,416 --> 00:10:49,250
[KAEDE]
He passed me.

210
00:10:51,416 --> 00:10:53,500
[KAEDE] There's no way
I can catch up with him!

211
00:10:53,583 --> 00:10:54,833
What now?!

212
00:10:54,916 --> 00:10:57,291
I could just follow behind
and trace his path.

213
00:10:57,375 --> 00:10:58,333
Huh?!

214
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,000
[KAEDE]
No, I can't give up!

215
00:11:01,083 --> 00:11:02,541
I've gotta push myself!

216
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:04,333
I'm worthy of
running against him!

217
00:11:04,416 --> 00:11:08,166
I know I can beat him if I
give it everything I've got!

218
00:11:08,625 --> 00:11:12,083
[KAEDE yells]

219
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:14,625
[NANA]
Get ready, Heath!

220
00:11:14,708 --> 00:11:16,250
They're pretty much
neck-and-neck!

221
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:18,625
Well, well looks like
that first-year of yours

222
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:19,875
has some skills.

223
00:11:19,958 --> 00:11:21,666
[NANA]
Get Set!

224
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:22,708
Three...

225
00:11:22,791 --> 00:11:23,666
Two...

226
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:24,708
One...

227
00:11:24,791 --> 00:11:25,750
Go!

228
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:32,291
[HEATH]
I'll take it from here!

229
00:11:32,375 --> 00:11:33,666
[KYOSUKE]
Heath.

230
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:37,583
It's all up to you now.
Make our last summer count!

231
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:47,000
[HEATH] There's no runnin'
side-by-side with this chump.

232
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:49,791
[TASUKU]
Why'd he back off so easily?

233
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:52,375
He's got something
up his sleeve.

234
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,208
[HEATH]
Jeez, that was a risky move.

235
00:11:59,291 --> 00:12:01,250
This is no time to be reckless.

236
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:05,041
Get injured in the semi-finals
and it's over for your team.

237
00:12:05,125 --> 00:12:06,916
[TASUKU] I'll do whatever
it takes to get ahead!

238
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,958
We've come too far
to lose to Honan!

239
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:11,666
This is Reiji's last shot
at winning End of Summer.

240
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:14,125
We have to do it for him!

241
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,041
[HEATH]
Fine, then.

242
00:12:17,125 --> 00:12:19,666
Two can play at that game.

243
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:21,916
I may be crazy for tryin' this,

244
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,708
but I've got to!

245
00:12:23,791 --> 00:12:25,750
If we lose this match it's over.

246
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:28,333
I won't let our summer end.

247
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:31,208
[HEATH]
Not yet!

248
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:34,666
[HEATH grunts]

249
00:12:40,958 --> 00:12:43,916
[NANA]
Hey, Riku. Can ya hear me?

250
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,250
[RIKU]
Yeah.

251
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:46,250
[NANA]
They're coming.

252
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,750
Let's win and go to finals.

253
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:50,666
It's all up to you now!

254
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:51,958
[RIKU inahles]

255
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:53,208
[TAKERU]
I'm confident

256
00:12:53,291 --> 00:12:56,041
that we'll win the End
of Summer tournament.

257
00:12:56,125 --> 00:12:57,958
Because we made a--

258
00:12:59,041 --> 00:13:00,083
[NANA]
Head's up!

259
00:13:00,166 --> 00:13:02,833
We're in the lead!
Point eight seconds!

260
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:05,916
[RIKU]
Got it!

261
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:09,791
Don't you worry, Takeru!

262
00:13:09,875 --> 00:13:12,166
I'll be there in no time!

263
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:15,458
[TAKERU]
Riku.

264
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:26,208
[panting]

265
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:27,708
[TAKERU]
It's no use!

266
00:13:27,791 --> 00:13:32,041
I'm running as fast as I can,
but it's not fast enough!

267
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:34,958
There's no way.
I'll run right into him!

268
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:36,291
[RIKU]
I know you can do it!

269
00:13:36,375 --> 00:13:38,083
Run, Takeru!

270
00:13:40,416 --> 00:13:41,958
[TAKERU]
Riku.

271
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:47,916
[ASUMA] The last half coming up
is all about endurance!

272
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,208
Luckily, it's also
Riku's weakness.

273
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:54,083
Which means it's time
to take it up to 11!

274
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:56,750
[RIKU] Asuma's haulin'!
I can barely keep up.

275
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,666
He's way faster than
he was back at the camp!

276
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:02,083
It doesn't matter!
I'm closin' in on him!

277
00:14:02,166 --> 00:14:03,875
I've gotta push it so we
can win this thing!

278
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,416
We have to!

279
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:09,708
I'm confident that we'll win
the End of Summer tournament.

280
00:14:09,791 --> 00:14:11,166
Because we made a--

281
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:13,583
[RIKU]
What'd he mean by that?

282
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:15,791
We made it our goal?

283
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:17,625
I mean, we did.

284
00:14:17,708 --> 00:14:20,208
But that's not it!

285
00:14:20,291 --> 00:14:21,333
[SHIZUMA]
Get ready, Reiji.

286
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:22,833
They're on their way.

287
00:14:23,625 --> 00:14:24,750
[SHIZUMA]
It's tight.

288
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:27,041
Riku doesn't seem to be
slowing down at all.

289
00:14:27,125 --> 00:14:29,250
In fact, he's right
on Asuma's heels.

290
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:30,958
It's up to you.

291
00:14:33,208 --> 00:14:34,791
[REIJI]
Shizuma.

292
00:14:37,166 --> 00:14:39,333
[REIJI]
We'll win, for sure.

293
00:14:39,416 --> 00:14:40,666
[gasps]

294
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,791
Of course we will.

295
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:45,708
--[NANA] Takeru, get set!
--Okay Reiji, get set!

296
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:48,125
[NANA]
We're 0.5 seconds behind!

297
00:14:48,583 --> 00:14:49,791
[RIKU panting]

298
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:52,166
[NANA] Oh no, don't start
slowing down now.

299
00:14:52,250 --> 00:14:53,916
Maybe I should wait
to make the call.

300
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:57,166
[TAKERU] Trust him!
I know he can do it!

301
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:01,000
[ANNOUNCER 11A]
Here we go, folks!

302
00:15:01,083 --> 00:15:03,833
The final relation is coming up!

303
00:15:04,375 --> 00:15:05,875
Three...

304
00:15:05,958 --> 00:15:07,416
Two...

305
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:09,000
One!

306
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:15,916
[TAKERU] I'm running as fast as
I can, but it's not fast enough!

307
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:16,958
He's slowing down!

308
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:18,708
[RIKU]
No! Don't give up!

309
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:21,250
I know you can do it!
Run, Takeru!

310
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:23,916
[TAKERU panting]

311
00:15:26,416 --> 00:15:27,916
[RIKU]
I'm totally spent.

312
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,791
I can't keep going much longer!

313
00:15:34,583 --> 00:15:36,125
I know you can do it, Riku!

314
00:15:36,208 --> 00:15:37,791
[panting]

315
00:15:41,291 --> 00:15:42,291
[RIKU]
Takeru!

316
00:15:42,375 --> 00:15:43,791
Go! Hurry!

317
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:46,041
[RIKU groaning]

318
00:16:03,875 --> 00:16:06,375
[RIKU groaning]
Takeru!

319
00:16:06,458 --> 00:16:08,291
Go! Hurry!

320
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:14,750
I remember.
It's all coming back.

321
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,000
[RIKU]
Good job, Takeru!

322
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:17,500
We make a great team!

323
00:16:17,583 --> 00:16:19,958
When we get older we're gonna
crush it at End of Summer!

324
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:21,083
[TAKERU]
Yeah!

325
00:16:22,666 --> 00:16:25,333
If you work really hard you'll
get faster than you are now!

326
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:27,791
Probably even faster than me!

327
00:16:27,875 --> 00:16:29,458
Do you think so?

328
00:16:29,541 --> 00:16:32,583
[laughs] 'Kay!

329
00:16:34,083 --> 00:16:36,125
[NANA]
Isn't Stride so much fun?

330
00:16:36,208 --> 00:16:38,208
[RIKU] Yeah! I'll bet
if we made a team

331
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:40,708
we could be the best
in the whole world!

332
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,375
[TAKERU]
I'll practice.

333
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:47,875
And then one day, the three of
us will be teammates for real!

334
00:16:47,958 --> 00:16:49,541
--[NANA] Yeah!
--[RIKU] 'Kay!

335
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:51,208
And then we could
enter End of Summer!

336
00:16:51,291 --> 00:16:52,458
That'd be awesome!

337
00:16:52,541 --> 00:16:54,541
But wait, that means
we'll have to go

338
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:56,250
to the same high school one day.

339
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:59,208
[RIKU] Okay! Let's see,
the only school from Tokyo

340
00:16:59,291 --> 00:17:02,291
that qualified for End of
Summer this year was...?

341
00:17:02,375 --> 00:17:03,791
[TAKERU]
Honan!

342
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:05,625
Honan Academy.

343
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:07,625
Yeah, let's go there!

344
00:17:07,708 --> 00:17:09,125
When we're old
and in high school,

345
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:10,958
we'll join the
Honan Stride Club!

346
00:17:11,041 --> 00:17:13,666
Then we can beat all the other
teams and win the End of Summer!

347
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:15,250
You think we can win?!

348
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:17,583
[RIKU] If we're gonna do it we
might as well aim for the top!

349
00:17:17,666 --> 00:17:20,875
If we work really hard,
I know we can win it!

350
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:21,500
[RIKU]
Yeah!

351
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:22,500
[NANA]
I'm in!

352
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,708
We're gonna win
the End of Summer!

353
00:17:24,791 --> 00:17:26,708
[ALL]
It's a promise!

354
00:17:27,750 --> 00:17:29,416
[TAKERU]
Yes!

355
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:32,208
I'm going to keep my promise!

356
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,458
[AYUMU gasps]

357
00:17:49,583 --> 00:17:50,791
Go, Reiji!

358
00:17:52,958 --> 00:17:55,166
[TAKERU panting]

359
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:56,458
[RIKU]
If you work really hard

360
00:17:56,541 --> 00:17:57,916
you'll get faster
than you are now!

361
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,250
[TAKERU]
I will!

362
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:00,666
[RIKU]
I'll bet if we made a team,

363
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,375
we could be the best
in the whole world!

364
00:18:02,458 --> 00:18:04,541
[TAKERU]
You were right, Riku.

365
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:08,958
[TAKERU]
It's just like you said.

366
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:14,791
[TAKERU]
We're the best!

367
00:18:22,250 --> 00:18:23,625
[ANNOUNCER 11A]
The winner is...

368
00:18:23,708 --> 00:18:27,458
...Honan Academy first-year
student, Takeru Fujiwara!

369
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:28,708
Incredible!

370
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:31,208
He beat Reiji Suwa
of Saisei High School

371
00:18:31,291 --> 00:18:34,083
by a mere fraction of a second!

372
00:18:42,166 --> 00:18:43,000
[RIKU]
Hey, buddy.

373
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:45,500
You know that's not good for ya.

374
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:47,041
How many times have you told me

375
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:48,500
you're supposed to catch your
breath before you collapse,

376
00:18:48,583 --> 00:18:50,041
huh? [laughs]

377
00:18:50,125 --> 00:18:51,333
[TAKERU chuckles]

378
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:03,041
It's like watching baby
birds leaving the nest.

379
00:19:03,125 --> 00:19:04,916
I thought these kinds
of emotional breakthroughs

380
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,166
only happened in the
best Shogi matches!

381
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:10,500
Hey now, don't start that,
you'll get me goin', too!

382
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:11,750
[HEATH]
This is a happy moment, man.

383
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:12,833
No need for waterworks.

384
00:19:12,916 --> 00:19:14,291
What makes you think
I'm crying?!

385
00:19:14,375 --> 00:19:15,875
Maybe it got really hot
on the bleachers

386
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:17,250
and I'm sweating from my eyes!

387
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:18,875
[HEATH] Okay, dude.
Whatever helps with the shame.

388
00:19:18,958 --> 00:19:22,041
[HOZUMI laughing]

389
00:19:22,125 --> 00:19:23,583
[HEATH]
Aw, man, did I make it worse?

390
00:19:23,666 --> 00:19:26,458
C'mon, pull it together, bro.

391
00:19:26,541 --> 00:19:28,166
[REIJI]
Nice work, Honan Stride.

392
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:31,125
Congratulations on
making it to the finals.

393
00:19:32,416 --> 00:19:35,625
We enjoyed racin' you today,
and I mean that.

394
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:37,666
We had a great time, as usual.

395
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:40,583
Thanks again for
everything you did for us.

396
00:19:40,666 --> 00:19:42,166
It was our pleasure, Heath.

397
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:44,666
Next you have to face Kakyoin.

398
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,583
You can bet we'll be rooting
for Honan all the way.

399
00:19:47,666 --> 00:19:49,000
Thanks.

400
00:19:49,083 --> 00:19:51,583
Oh, and Takeru, I can't
wait to see you outrun

401
00:19:51,666 --> 00:19:54,750
every athlete at the finals.
You're an incredible talent.

402
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,125
Thanks.

403
00:19:56,208 --> 00:19:56,916
[ASUMA]
Riku!

404
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:57,958
[RIKU]
Uh.

405
00:19:59,583 --> 00:20:00,916
Ow, be careful, bro!

406
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,666
[ASUMA]
I'm so proud of you!

407
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:06,708
You remember that at the finals.
It's all up to you.

408
00:20:06,791 --> 00:20:09,333
Promise you'll put your heart
and soul into winning!

409
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,208
[RIKU gasps]

410
00:20:14,583 --> 00:20:15,916
[RIKU]
I will.

411
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,083
You bet I will!

412
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:34,541
[REIJI]
Congratulations, Honan Stride!

413
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:36,125
Time to celebrate!

414
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:38,500
Here is a special
song just for you!

415
00:20:38,583 --> 00:20:42,791
[GALAXY STANDARD singing]

416
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,458
[NANA]
Beautiful!

417
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:15,166
To think I first met you
guys seven years ago.

418
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:18,791
And at an EOS pre-party,
too. It's crazy, huh?

419
00:22:18,875 --> 00:22:21,375
Yeah, it was all new to me.

420
00:22:21,458 --> 00:22:23,833
I'd never heard
of Stride before.

421
00:22:23,916 --> 00:22:25,208
[RIKU]
Good job, Takeru!

422
00:22:25,291 --> 00:22:26,708
We make a great team!

423
00:22:26,791 --> 00:22:29,541
When we get older we're gonna
crush it at End of Summer!

424
00:22:29,625 --> 00:22:31,291
[NANA]
I'm sorry that I forgot!

425
00:22:31,375 --> 00:22:32,791
[RIKU]
Yeah, me too, man!

426
00:22:32,875 --> 00:22:34,166
But to be fair,

427
00:22:34,250 --> 00:22:36,083
you look way different thank
you did seven years ago!

428
00:22:36,166 --> 00:22:38,625
Well, except for the stoic
look and the glasses.

429
00:22:38,708 --> 00:22:40,083
Okay. My bad.

430
00:22:40,166 --> 00:22:43,750
Sorry it took me this
long to recognize you.

431
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:45,416
Are we cool?

432
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,125
I'm not upset that you forgot.

433
00:22:47,208 --> 00:22:49,083
All that matters is the
three of us are together

434
00:22:49,166 --> 00:22:52,833
doing stride again.
Just like we said we would.

435
00:22:52,916 --> 00:22:54,083
You may not remember,

436
00:22:54,166 --> 00:22:56,375
but we made a promise
to one another that day,

437
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:59,041
and I want to make it a reality.

438
00:22:59,125 --> 00:23:01,125
We promised to win
End of Summer someday.

439
00:23:01,208 --> 00:23:03,000
Didn't we?

440
00:23:03,083 --> 00:23:04,291
Yeah.

441
00:23:05,291 --> 00:23:07,583
I think we should make
the promise again tonight!

442
00:23:07,666 --> 00:23:10,458
Agreed! This year the three
of us and our team,

443
00:23:10,541 --> 00:23:13,208
Honan Stride, are gonna
win the End of Summer!

444
00:23:13,291 --> 00:23:14,708
[TAKERU, NANA]
Yeah!

445
00:23:14,791 --> 00:23:17,041
[ALL]
It's a promise!

446
00:23:17,125 --> 00:23:22,000
[ALL laughing]

447
00:23:28,375 --> 00:23:29,708
[RIKU]
Hey, guys.

448
00:23:29,791 --> 00:23:32,000
I have something to confess.

449
00:23:32,083 --> 00:23:33,708
[NANA]
Huh?

450
00:23:33,791 --> 00:23:34,875
I've been thinking,

451
00:23:34,958 --> 00:23:38,375
and I've decided I
wanna run against Tomoe.

452
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:39,458
[TAKERU, NANA gasp]

453
00:23:39,541 --> 00:23:41,375
You sure about that?

454
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:47,458
I'm not running away anymore.

455
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:00,125
[TAKERU]
Good.

456
00:24:07,833 --> 00:24:09,916
[REIJI] All right Honan,
we only ask one thing.

457
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,208
Please accept the well wishes

458
00:24:11,291 --> 00:24:12,791
of the Galaxy Standard
"Beautiful Eight."

459
00:24:12,875 --> 00:24:13,958
[HEATH]
"Beautiful Eight"?

460
00:24:14,041 --> 00:24:15,041
[REIJI] What, don't you
find us beautiful?

461
00:24:15,125 --> 00:24:16,166
[SHIZUMA]
Allow me to explain,

462
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:17,750
the seventh generation
of Gal-Stan,

463
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:19,875
the one before us, was
called the "Exotic Seven."

464
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:22,000
[REIJI]
<i>Je t'aime</i> , Andromeda.

